    <title>Transitive membership perf integration tests + p95 check</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
      Authored canary perf integration test
      `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Membership/TransitiveMembershipPerfTests.cs`
      mirroring task 054's fixture (`TransitiveMembershipIntegrationFixture` —
      WebApplicationFactory + mocked `IMembershipResolverService` + fake auth handler).

      Fixture scale (NFR-04 envelope):
        - 500 seeded primary memberships ("sprk_matter").
        - 5 documents per matter → 2500 transitive document IDs in a single response.

      Measurement protocol:
        - 10 warmup iterations (timings discarded — WAF JIT, route table, JSON metadata cache settle).
        - 100 measured iterations (per-call elapsed-ms via `Stopwatch`).
        - Distributional stats computed via nearest-rank (R-1) percentile.

      Measured (single CI-class runner, in-process, mocked resolver):
        - p50 =   0 ms
        - p95 =   1 ms
        - p99 =   7 ms
        - max =   8 ms
        - mean=   0.3 ms

      Soft 300ms NFR-04 target: **MET in-process** (p95 1ms &lt;&lt; 300ms).
      Hard 3000ms gross-regression gate (asserted): **PASS**.

      Per AC-1A.5 (owner clarification 2026-06-20) the canonical production NFR-04
      measurement is via **Application Insights server-side request telemetry** —
      this in-process test is a canary regression catcher, NOT the production
      measurement. The mocked resolver returns instantly so the measurement
      isolates the BFF pipeline overhead (auth, routing, JSON serialization at
      transitive scale, ProblemDetails handling). No production performance limit
      observed in-process that would require documenting in spec.md AC-1D.2.

      Asymmetric-registration (bff-extensions.md §F.1): NOT TRIGGERED — no DI
      module touched, no new service registered, test-only addition.

      Test results: 1 new test (passes); full integration suite 64/64 pass (0 failures,
      0 regressions). Build: 0 errors, 16 warnings (all pre-existing in unrelated modules,
      not introduced by this task).

      No BFF source code modified → no publish-size verification required; no NuGet
      package added → no CVE recheck required.
